ksi-tool
------------------------------------------
KSI command-line tool enables the access to the KSI blockchain and its
functions from the shell. It can be used for signing data in files or other
sources, extending existing KSI signatures and verifying them using different
trust anchors.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-0.203.gf78009cb1ccf
  libksi13-3.21.3087-1bl1
  libparamset2-1.1.244-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libksi-devel-3.21.3087-1bl1
  libparamset-devel-1.1.244-1bl1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/guardtime/ksi-tool

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/guardtime/ksi-tool/archive/refs/tags/v2.10.1387.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ksi-tool-2.10.1387-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ksi-tool-2.10.1387-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ksi-tool-2.10.1387-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ksi-tool-2.10.1387-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

